stylometry: SUMPRODUCT allows us to add up all of the numbers produces. For example, you take column A row one X column B row one + column A row two X column B row two + column A row three X column B row three + ... until you have your final sumproduct. VLOOKUP takes all the inputs in the far most left column of the table and returns and output in the first row based on cost index. SUMIF adds up all the outputs given certain criteria. IF returns an output if the statement is to be evaluated as true or returns another set of outputs if the statement is to be evaluated as false.
